# Sports Nomenclature Rules

## 1. Football Disambiguation (CRITICAL)

**The term "Football" is AMBIGUOUS and MUST NOT be used alone.**

| Input Term | Canonical Sport | Examples |
|------------|-----------------|----------|
| Football | **AMBIGUOUS - DO NOT USE** | - |
| Soccer | Soccer | Premier League, MLS, La Liga |
| Association Football | Soccer | FIFA, UEFA competitions |
| American Football | American Football | NFL, NCAA, CFL |
| Gridiron | American Football | XFL, USFL |

### Rules
- NEVER use standalone "Football" in code, comments, database fields, or data structures
- ALWAYS map league names to explicit sport types before processing
- When source data is ambiguous, check secondary features (pitch dimensions, quarters vs halves)

